  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Breast cancer is one of the most common cancer among women nowadays. There are lots of
      modality of treatment and one of them is Mastectomy. We found out that seroma is one of the
      disturbing postoperative complications after mastectomy. In our study we want to compare the
      outcome between using the conventional electrocautery and the low thermal tissue dissection.
      We expected that the serum production should be lower in cases using low thermal system
      electrosurgery system.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
